TableBuilder
============

Builder for creating tables inspired by ActionView::Helpers::FormHelper::FormBuilder.

Example
=======

<% table_for([FrontMan.new(1, 'David St. Hubbins')]) do |t| %>
  <%= t.head('Name') %>
  <% t.body_r do |e| %>
    <%= t.d(h(e.name)) %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>

All tags can have extra html options.

@drummers = [Drummer.new(1, 'John "Stumpy" Pepys'), Drummer.new(2, 'Eric "Stumpy Joe" Childs')]

<% table_for(@drummers, :html => { :id => 'spinal_tap', :class => 'drummers'}) do |t| %>
  <% t.body_r do |e| %>
    <%= t.d(h(e.id), :class => 'class') %>
    <%= t.d(h(e.name)) %>
  <% end %>
<% end %> 

Produces the following html:

<table class="drummers" id="spinal_tap">
  <tbody><tr>
    <td class="class">1</td>
    <td>John &quot;Stumpy&quot; Pepys</td>
  </tr><tr>
    <td class="class">2</td>
    <td>Eric &quot;Stumpy Joe&quot; Childs</td>
  </tr></tbody>
</table>

Install
=======

script/plugin install git://github.com/p8/table_builder.git


